'''Andorra''''s entry for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006]] was chosen in an internal selection by national broadcaster [[Ràdio i Televisió d'Andorra|RTVA]]. From over 44 candidates, the selectors chose [[Jenny (singer)|Jenny]], with the song "[[Sense tu]]" (Without you), which they described as similar to the music of artists such as [[Sam Brown (singer)|Sam Brown]] and [[Anastacia]].

Jenny was born in [[Asturias]], [[Spain]], and was a student of music under [[Helen Rowson]] in [[Barcelona]]. She was a new artist in both [[Spain]] and Andorra, with no previous commercial success in either country. The [[record producer|producer]] of this, as well as the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2005|2005 entry]], was [[Rafael Artesero]].

Not having advanced to the final in [[Eurovision Song Contest 2005|2005]], Andorra had to compete in the semifinal in 2006 as well. As both previous Andorran entries, it fared quite poorly. Jenny failed to qualify to the final as well, finishing last of the 23 semifinal contestants.

