The '''Belgian Society of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology''' (BMB) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] non-profit organization, concerned with [[biochemistry]] and [[molecular biology]].<ref name=icp-ucl>{{cite web|title=Belgian Society of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology|url=http://www.icp.ucl.ac.be/bsbmb2/home.html|publisher=icp.ucl.ac.be|accessdate=22 March 2014}}</ref> <ref name=febs>{{cite web|title=The Belgian Society of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology|url=http://www.febs.org/our-members/the-belgian-society-of-biochemistry-and-molecular-biology|publisher=febs.org|accessdate=22 March 2014}}</ref>
The BMB was created, based on an initiative of [[Marcel Florkin]], so a Belgian society could join the new [[International Union of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology|International Union of Biochemistry]]. The first charter of the society was drafted by [[Edouard J. Bigwood]], [[Jean Brachet]], [[Christian de Duve]], Marcel Florkin, [[Lucien Massart]], [[Paul Putzeys]], [[Laurent Vandendriessche]] and [[Claude Lièbecq]]. The first general assembly was held on 12 January 1952, and the first President of the society was Marcel Florkin, with Claude Lièbecq as secretary and treasurer.<ref name=biochemistry>{{cite web|title=Belgian Society of Biochemistry and M|url=http://www.biochemistry.be/liebecq.pdf|publisher=biochemistry.be|accessdate=22 March 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102182234/http://www.biochemistry.be//liebecq.pdf|archivedate=2 November 2013|df=}}</ref> <ref name=healthcare>{{cite web|title=Belgian Society of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology Mo|url=http://www.healthcare.reachinformation.com/Belgian%20Society%20of%20Biochemistry%20and%20Molecular%20Biology.aspx|publisher=healthcare.reachinformation.com|accessdate=22 March 2014}}</ref>
