'''Buleusa''' is a populated place in the [[Walikale Territory]], the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].<ref name="rfirdcabuleusala">{{cite news|title=[Reportage] RDC: à Buleusa, la difficile attente d'un retour à une vie "normale"|url=http://www.rfi.fr/afrique/20160627-rdc-buleusa-fdlr-monusco-arme-congolaise-tension-incendie-communaute-kobo|accessdate=February 20, 2017|work=Radio France International|date=July 27, 2016}}</ref> It is home to a military camp run by the [[Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo]].<ref name="rfirdcabuleusala"/> In June 2016, between 3,000 and 4,000 [[Hutu]]s were refugees in the camp; they were hiding from the Kobos, who were trying to chase them away from the territory.<ref name="rfirdcabuleusala"/>

