'''Childless Hundred Days''' (百日无孩) is a campaign of mass forced [[abortion]] in [[Shen County]] and [[Guan County, Shandong|Guan County]] in [[Shandong]], China. The campaign started in [[1 May]], [[1991]] and ended in [[10 August]], [[1991]]. It was designed to reduce local population growth, under the national [[One-child policy]]. The campaign was initiated by the local [[Party Committee Secretary]] Zeng Zhaoqi (曾昭起) and Bai Zhigang (白志刚). <ref>{{cite web|title=新中国旧故事：山东的百日无孩运动|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/111413012_119977}}</ref> 

During the campaign, local officials were asked to perform forced abortion on any pregnant woman in these areas regardless of pregnancy terms or whether the unborn child is the first child of the family. The policy led to mass panic and dramatic reduction of local population in 1991. <ref>{{cite web|title=计生委前司长：中国妇女为计生牺牲很大 政府应予回报|url=http://news.ifeng.com/mainland/detail_2012_06/14/15293074_0.shtml}}</ref>

