'''Prefection''',{{sfn|Fügedi|1998|p=53}}{{sfn|Rady|2000|p=107}} also '''promotion of a daughter to a son'''{{sfn|Engel|2001|p=178}} ({{lang-hu|fiúsítás}}; {{lang-la|praefectio in filium}}), was a [[royal prerogative]] in the [[Kingdom of Hungary]], whereby the [[King of Hungary|sovereign]] granted the status of a son to a [[Hungarian nobility|nobleman]]'s daughter, authorizing her to inherit her father's landed property.

