'''Ruse Iztok Thermal Power Plant''' ({{lang-bg|ТЕЦ Русе Изток}}) is a power plant situated near the city of [[Ruse, Bulgaria|Ruse]], [[Bulgaria]]. It has an installed capacity of 400 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]]. It is owned by [[Holding Slovenske elektrarne]].<ref name=iht> {{cite news | title= Slovenian energy company buys heating utility in Bulgaria for €81 million | publisher = International Herald tribune | url = http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2007/08/28/business/EU-FIN-Bulgaria-Energy.php | date = 2007-08-28 | accessdate = 2009-02-21}} </ref> Ruse Iztok Power Plant has 3 chimneys, from which 2 have a height of 180 metres and 1 has a height of 140 metres.
