'''Zeng Liansong''' ({{zh|t=曾聯松|s=曾联松|p=Zēng Liánsōng}}) (December 17, 1917 － October 19, 1999) was the designer of the [[Flag of the People's Republic of China]].<ref name="cbw">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbw.com/btm/issue71/62-63.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=November 3, 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090211184343/http://www.cbw.com/btm/issue71/62-63.html |archivedate=February 11, 2009 }}</ref><ref name="sb9">http://www.s9.com/Biography/Zeng-Liansong</ref> He was from [[Ruian]], [[Wenzhou]], [[Zhejiang]] province.<ref name="cbw"/><ref name="sb9"/>

He entered the [[economics]] department at the National Central University ([[Nanjing University]]) in 1936.<ref name="sb9"/><ref>National Central University renamed Nanjing University in 1949.</ref>  During the [[Second Sino-Japanese War]], he participated in confrontation against [[Empire of Japan|Japanese]] forces. He was also a member of the standing committee of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference|CPPCC]] [[Shanghai]] committee.

He died in 1999, aged 81.<ref name="sb9"/>

